ollowing her plea of not guilty, Magistrate O.A. Akokhia, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N20,000 with two sureties in like sum. Akokhia ordered that the sureties must be gainfully employed and show evidence of two years tax payment to the Lagos State Government. The magistrate adjourned the case until Jan. 16. Vanguard News Nigeria A trader, Tope Akinside, on Friday appeared in an Ikeja Magistrates' Court, Lagos, for allegedly beating and bathing her neighbour with faeces. March 4, 2016 In "News" A 26-year-old woman, Ada Egole, on Tuesday appeared in an Apapa Chief Magistrates' Court, Lagos, for allegedly pouring faeces on her neighbour’s body. April 12, 2016 In "News" A 43-year-old guest, Donnie Egbuzie, on Thursday appeared before an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court for allegedly inflicting injuries on a woman over her son’s refusal to greet him. December 27, 2018 In "News"